To compile, run:
 % gcc -lzmq testcase.c
 % chmod +x a.out
 % ./a.out

On OSX & Linux, should print something similar to:

Chuck-Remess-Mac-Pro:2-1 cremes$ ./a.out
worker has started
worker has started
Sending tasks to workers...
Successfully sent [330] messages
EAGAIN received for [999670] messages


On Windows, it should print something like:
$ ./a.out
worker has started
worker has started
Sending tasks to workers...
Successfully sent [1000000] messages
EAGAIN received for [0] messages


